# Generated token file — always LF so regeneration produces a stable diff
# and the committed copy never shows CRLF churn against the build output.
public/eq-tokens.css text eol=lf

# Tenant migrations are content-hashed by the One Pipe runner. Force LF on every
# checkout (Windows included) so a migration applied locally and one applied in
# CI produce the SAME checksum — otherwise CRLF vs LF yields phantom drift in
# app_data._eq_migrations. The runner also LF-normalises before hashing as a
# belt-and-suspenders, but pinning EOL here keeps the working tree honest too.
supabase/tenant-migrations/*.sql text eol=lf
